      },
      "methods": [],
      "module_path": "task_contract",
      "docs": "Domain model for task-contract.json. Maps each TaskId in the active track to the catalogue entries (layer + entry_key pairs) that the task is responsible for implementing. Validated at construction: track_id must be non-empty (enforced by TrackId), entries map must be non-empty, and every task must carry at least one contracted entry.",
      "spec_refs": [
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "IN-01" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "AC-01" }
      ],
      "informal_grounds": []
    },
    "ContractedEntryRef": {
      "action": "add",
      "role": { "ValueObject": {} },
      "kind": {
        "kind": "struct",
        "shape": {
          "kind": "plain",
          "fields": [],
          "has_stripped_fields": true
        }
      },
      "methods": [],
      "module_path": "task_contract",
      "docs": "A (layer, entry_key) pair identifying one catalogue entry contracted to a task. Distinct from domain::tddd::semantic_verify::CatalogueEntryRef (which holds file_path + section_key + entry_key for spec-adr verification). This type carries only the layer identity and catalogue entry key needed for the pre-review gate check. Fields (layer: LayerId, entry_key: CatalogueEntryKey) are pub(crate) and thus stripped in rustdoc; accessed via the layer() and entry_key() getter methods.",
      "spec_refs": [
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "IN-01" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "CN-01" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "CN-02" }
      ],
      "informal_grounds": []
    },
    "PreReviewGateViolation": {
      "action": "add",
      "role": { "ValueObject": {} },
      "kind": {
        "kind": "enum",
        "variants": [
          {
            "name": "MissingTaskContract",
            "payload": { "kind": "unit" }
          },
          {
            "name": "NonBlueSignal",
            "payload": {
              "kind": "struct",
              "fields": [
                { "name": "entry", "ty": "ContractedEntryRef" },
                { "name": "signal", "ty": "ConfidenceSignal" }
              ]
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "methods": [],
      "module_path": "task_contract",
      "docs": "A single liveness-gate violation found during `bin/sotp task-contract check`. Narrowed to check-specific violations after D5 split: MissingTaskContract (task-contract.json absent, gate cannot proceed) and NonBlueSignal (an attributed entry fails the D7 liveness rule: current/done task ownership with a non-blue impl_catalog signal, or todo-only ownership with a red signal; todo-only yellow is tolerated). Attribution violations (OrphanEntry, InvalidEntryRef) moved to CoverageViolation used by the coverage subcommand. Modelled as a finding record (ValueObject), not an error type: it is data carried inside PreReviewGateOutcome::Blocked.",
      "spec_refs": [
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "IN-04" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "CN-03" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "CN-07" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "GO-03" }
      ],
      "informal_grounds": []
    },
    "PreReviewGateOutcome": {
      "action": "add",
      "role": { "ValueObject": {} },
      "kind": {
        "kind": "enum",
        "variants": [
          {
            "name": "Passed",
            "payload": { "kind": "unit" }
          },
          {
            "name": "Blocked",
            "payload": {
              "kind": "struct",
              "fields": [
                { "name": "violations", "ty": "Vec<PreReviewGateViolation>" }
              ]
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "methods": [],
      "module_path": "task_contract",
      "docs": "Outcome of the `bin/sotp task-contract check` liveness gate. Passed is a binary OK signal: all current/done attributed entries have blue impl_catalog signals and no todo-only attributed entry has a red signal (todo-only yellow is tolerated). Blocked carries the list of liveness violations (MissingTaskContract, NonBlueSignal). The Blocked variant is #[non_exhaustive]. Use PreReviewGateOutcome::blocked() to construct a Blocked outcome so the non-empty invariant is checked.",
      "spec_refs": [
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "IN-04" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "GO-03" }
      ],
      "informal_grounds": []
    },
    "CoverageViolation": {
      "action": "add",
      "role": { "ValueObject": {} },
      "kind": {
        "kind": "enum",
        "variants": [
          {
            "name": "MissingTaskContract",
            "payload": { "kind": "unit" }
          },
          {
            "name": "OrphanEntry",
            "payload": {
              "kind": "struct",
              "fields": [
                { "name": "entry", "ty": "ContractedEntryRef" }
              ]
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "InvalidEntryRef",
            "payload": {
              "kind": "struct",
              "fields": [
                { "name": "entry", "ty": "ContractedEntryRef" },
                { "name": "reason", "ty": "String" }
              ]
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "methods": [],
      "module_path": "task_contract",
      "docs": "A single attribution-completeness violation found during `bin/sotp task-contract coverage`. MissingTaskContract: task-contract.json is absent so coverage cannot check anything (fail-closed). OrphanEntry: a catalogue entry exists but is not attributed to any task in task-contract.json (attribution completeness failure). InvalidEntryRef: an entry attributed in task-contract.json does not exist in the current catalogue (referential integrity failure). InvalidEntryRef.reason is an opaque diagnostic string (R9 exception: error message). These violations are data inside CoverageVerifyOutcome::Blocked.",
      "spec_refs": [
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "IN-03" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "IN-07" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "CN-01" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "CN-02" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "CN-07" }
      ],
      "informal_grounds": []
    },
    "CoverageVerifyOutcome": {
      "action": "add",
      "role": { "ValueObject": {} },
      "kind": {
        "kind": "enum",
        "variants": [
          {
            "name": "Passed",
            "payload": { "kind": "unit" }
          },
          {
            "name": "Blocked",
            "payload": {
              "kind": "struct",
              "fields": [
                { "name": "violations", "ty": "Vec<CoverageViolation>" }
              ]
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "methods": [],
      "module_path": "task_contract",
      "docs": "Outcome of the `bin/sotp task-contract coverage` attribution-completeness check. Passed: all catalogue entries are attributed to at least one task, and all attributed entries exist in the catalogue. Blocked carries the list of attribution violations (MissingTaskContract, OrphanEntry, InvalidEntryRef). The Blocked variant is #[non_exhaustive]. Use CoverageVerifyOutcome::blocked() to construct a Blocked outcome so the non-empty invariant is checked.",
      "spec_refs": [
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "IN-07" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "AC-06" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "AC-08" }
      ],
      "informal_grounds": []
    }
